HEADWORD: Schreibersite
<hw>Schrei"bers*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
Carl von <ets>Schreibers</ets>, of Vienna.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral occurring in steel-gray flexible folia. It contains iron,
nickel, and phosphorus, and is found only in meteoric iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Schrode</ent>⟦br⟧
